==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lawsonia
<hw>Law*so"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>An Asiatic and North African shrub (<spn>Lawsonia inermis</spn>),
with smooth oval leaves, and fragrant white flowers. <prod>Henna</prod>
is prepared from the leaves and twigs. In England the shrub is called
<altname>Egyptian privet</altname>, and in the West Indies,
<altname>Jamaica mignonette</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lawsuit</ent>⟦br⟧
